@database rzxtool
@master "rzxtool.1"
@remark "manual page source format generated by PolyglotMan v3.2 available at http://polyglotman.sourceforge.net/"
@wordwrap
@tab 8
   
@node sect0 "Name"
rzxtool - Modify Sinclair ZX Spectrum input recording files    
@endnode

@node sect1 "Synopsis"
 @{b}rzxtool@{ub} [-d@{i}block number@{ui}]@{i}@{ui} [-e@{i}block number@{ui},@{i}filename@{ui}]@{i}@{ui} [-i@{i}block number@{ui},@{i}filename@{ui}]@{i}@{ui} [-u] @{i}rzxfile@{ui} [@{i}outfile@{ui}]@{i}@{ui}     


@endnode

@node sect2 "Description"
rzxtool allows some simple modifications to be made to Sinclair ZX Spectrum input recording files: blocks can be removed, snapshot data can be extracted or snapshots can be inserted into the file. The file can also be uncompressed.    
@endnode

@node sect3 "Options"
-d@{i}block number@{ui} @{lindent 3}
The block number specified will be deleted from the file. Block numbers start at zero and ignore any "creator information" blocks in the file. The modified file will be written to @{i}outfile@{ui}. @{lindent 0}
-e@{i}block number@{ui},@{i}filename@{ui} @{lindent 3}
The snapshot in the specified block number will be written to the specified filename. All snapshot formats supported by @{i}libspectrum@{ui}(3) are available. @{lindent 0}


-i@{i}block number@{ui},@{i}filename@{ui} @{lindent 3}
The snapshot specified in @{i}filename@{ui} will be added to the file at the position specified by @{i}block number@{ui}. @{lindent 0}


-u @{lindent 3}
When outputting an RZX file, this option causes the input recording data to be output uncompressed; if this option is not given, the data will be compressed using @{i}zlib@{ui}(3). @{lindent 0}


@{i}rzxfile@{ui} @{lindent 3}
specifies an input recording file whose contents are to be modified. @{lindent 0}


@{i}outfile@{ui} @{lindent 3}
specifies where the modified input file should be written. @{lindent 0}
   


@endnode

@node sect4 "Bugs"
None known    
@endnode

@node sect5 "See Also"
@{i}fuse@{ui}(1), @{i}fuse-utils@{ui}(1), @{i}rzxcheck@{ui}(1), @{i}rzxdump@{ui}(1), @{i}zlib@{ui}(3) The comp.sys.sinclair Spectrum FAQ, at 
@{i}http://www.worldofspectrum.org/faq/index.html@{ui}.    


@endnode

